  <prompt>
    Rewrite `docs/guides/BUILD-A-NEW-WORKSPACE-WIDGET.md` around a two-wrapper decision tree:
    (1) composable section in a dashboard (Pattern D), (2) sophisticated single-purpose direct widget,
    (3) dual-use widget (both shared lib + thin LW shim, e.g., Calendar), (4) Context-pane widget,
    (5) modal-launcher. Corrects terminology to match the W-1 doc. Retains and updates the existing
    Pattern D Calendar worked example. Future widget authors should be able to pick the right wrapper
    from the decision tree without back-channel.
  </prompt>

  <role>
    Technical writer with hands-on widget-author perspective. Optimize the guide for a developer who has
    never built a SpaarkeAi widget — they must reach the right wrapper choice in ≤5 minutes of reading.
  </role>

  <goal>
    `docs/guides/BUILD-A-NEW-WORKSPACE-WIDGET.md` rewritten with: (1) opening two-wrapper decision tree
    that branches to the five widget archetypes; (2) updated terminology matching `SPAARKEAI-DASHBOARD-AND-WIDGET-MODEL.md`
    (010); (3) retained + updated Pattern D Calendar worked example (shipped R3 tasks 114 + 115);
    (4) cross-link from this guide to W-1 model doc and back; (5) explicit anti-patterns (e.g., "do not invent a
    third wrapper", "do not duplicate section code in both LW and SpaarkeAi").
  </goal>

  <context>
    <background>
      Per spec DR-02 + plan §4 Phase 1 W-2: the existing widget-build guide predates the two-wrapper framing
      and uses inconsistent terminology. The R3 Calendar widget shipped a clean dual-use pattern (task 115
