  <steps>
    <step order="1" name="Read W-1 + existing guide">Read the new W-1 doc (010 output) and the existing guide. Catalog terminology mismatches between the two.</step>
    <step order="2" name="Draft decision tree">Write the opening decision tree as a flowchart (mermaid or numbered Q&amp;A): "Is this a composable section in a multi-section dashboard?" → Pattern D / dual-use; "Is this a sophisticated single-purpose tool?" → direct widget; "Does this need to render in Context pane?" → Context-pane widget; "Is this a modal launcher?" → modal pattern.</step>
    <step order="3" name="Rewrite archetype sections">For each of the five archetypes, write a short section: when to use, where the code lives, how to register. Reuse Calendar (Pattern D / dual-use) as the worked example.</step>
    <step order="4" name="Update Calendar worked example">Refresh the existing Pattern D Calendar walkthrough to reference current code (`src/client/shared/Spaarke.events-components/` + `calendar.registration.ts`) and the new model doc.</step>
    <step order="5" name="Add anti-patterns + cross-links">Add a short "Anti-patterns" section (do not invent a third wrapper, do not duplicate section code) and reciprocal cross-link to W-1.</step>
    <step order="6" name="Verify">Walk through the decision tree with 3 hypothetical widgets (one composable, one direct, one Context-pane) and confirm the tree reaches the right answer each time.</step>
    <step order="7" name="Update TASK-INDEX">Change task 011 status to ✅ completed in `tasks/TASK-INDEX.md`.</step>
    <step order="8" name="Document deviations">If any deviation from spec DR-02 or plan §4, write to `projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r4/notes/`.</step>
  </steps>

